Part 3 - Cybersecurity Research

Breach:
-2014 Yahoo data breach of 3B accounts
-Hackers traded information for bitcoin

Tech Flaws:
-Confidential data was not encrypted
-Employee network was not secure

Hacker method(s):
-Gained access to Yahoo's network through phishing scheme
-Yahoo employee w/ network access clicked on malicious link

Company action taken:
-Provide cyber security education to non-cyber security employees
-Ensure that basic security measures are in place (i.e. encryption of identifying information)
--Invalidated unencrypted security questions and answers
--Continually enhanced the systems that detect and prevent unauthorized access
--Required all affected and unaffected users to change their passwords